  <div class="about-statement">
    <p>Zach Miller is an artist based in Oklahoma City working primarily in painting, drawing, printmaking, and new media. His practice centers on the relationship between surface, duration, and the accumulated evidence of sustained looking.</p>
    <p>Working across extended periods, each painting develops through layers of application and removal — building a material history that becomes the subject itself. The work resists quick resolution in favor of a slower, more uncertain process where form emerges through repetition and revision.</p>
    <p>Miller's work explores the tension between physical presence and pictorial illusion, finding meaning in the accumulated marks and erasures that constitute a painting's history.</p>
  </div>

